# Implement Game History Module

## Context
Undo/redo is essential for:
- Player comfort (fix mistakes)
- Visual timeline feature
- GIF export (replay solution)
- Learning (backtrack and try different approach)

## API Design (shared/history.js)
```javascript
/**
 * Manages game state history for undo/redo functionality
 */
export class GameHistory {
  constructor(maxSize = 100) {
    this.states = [];
    this.currentIndex = -1;
    this.maxSize = maxSize;
  }

  /**
   * Push new state onto history
   * Truncates any "redo" states if not at end
   */
  push(state) {
    // Remove any states after current position
    this.states = this.states.slice(0, this.currentIndex + 1);

    // Add new state (deep clone)
    this.states.push(structuredClone(state));
    this.currentIndex++;

    // Enforce max size
    if (this.states.length > this.maxSize) {
      this.states.shift();
      this.currentIndex--;
    }
  }

  /**
   * Go back one state
   * @returns {Object|null} Previous state or null if at beginning
   */
  undo() {
    if (this.currentIndex > 0) {
      this.currentIndex--;
      return structuredClone(this.states[this.currentIndex]);
    }
    return null;
  }

  /**
   * Go forward one state
   * @returns {Object|null} Next state or null if at end
   */
  redo() {
    if (this.currentIndex < this.states.length - 1) {
      this.currentIndex++;
      return structuredClone(this.states[this.currentIndex]);
    }
    return null;
  }

  /**
   * Jump to specific state by index
   */
  jumpTo(index) {
    if (index >= 0 && index < this.states.length) {
      this.currentIndex = index;
      return structuredClone(this.states[index]);
    }
    return null;
  }

  /**
   * Get current state
   */
  current() {
    if (this.currentIndex >= 0) {
      return structuredClone(this.states[this.currentIndex]);
    }
    return null;
  }

  /**
   * Check if undo is available
   */
  canUndo() {
    return this.currentIndex > 0;
  }

  /**
   * Check if redo is available
   */
  canRedo() {
    return this.currentIndex < this.states.length - 1;
  }

  /**
   * Get all states for timeline visualization
   */
  getTimeline() {
    return this.states.map((state, i) => ({
      index: i,
      state: structuredClone(state),
      isCurrent: i === this.currentIndex
    }));
  }

  /**
   * Clear all history
   */
  clear() {
    this.states = [];
    this.currentIndex = -1;
  }

  /**
   * Get current length
   */
  get length() {
    return this.states.length;
  }
}
```

## Testing Requirements
- Test push/undo/redo cycle
- Test timeline after branching (undo then new move)
- Test max size enforcement
- Test deep cloning (mutations don't affect history)

